13/08/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina(BiH) -- Police arrested on Wednesday (August 12th) a 20-year-old Bosnian man who confessed to firing shots at St. Nicholas Orthodox church in the Sarajevo suburb of Reljevo. No one was injured in the incident, which happened in the early hours of the morning. Bosnian Serb officials condemned the incident and insisted on bringing those responsible to justice. (RTRS, Srna, Fena, Sarajevo-x.com, Nezavisne Novine - 12/08/09)
